  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6578 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6500 (-4.6B) and max positive gamma at 6600 (+2.2B), dealers are in active hedging mode - they just bought the move up from 6500 and will need to sell if we push toward 6600. The wall_break and gex_surge events combined with the massive negative GEX concentration below current levels creates a highly unstable setup where any downside move will trigger accelerated dealer buying. Key resistance at 6600 where dealer selling pressure kicks in, while support at 6575/6570 represents critical negative gamma walls that could provide explosive upside fuel if broken.\n\n**Bottom line:** Market is primed for big moves in either direction with dealers amplifying whatever breaks first.",
